docs.title: 1dplot
docs.description: Graphs the columns of a *.1D time series file to the X11 screen, or to an image file (.jpg or .png).

docs.title: Time Series Files
docs.description: Input time series files (*.1D) to be plotted.

docs.title: Install Colormap
docs.description: Install a new X11 colormap.

docs.title: Separate Sub-Graphs
docs.description: Plot each column in a separate sub-graph.

docs.title: One Big Graph
docs.description: Plot all columns together in one big graph.

docs.title: Separate Sub-Graphs with different y-scale
docs.description: Plot each column in a separate sub-graph and allow each sub-graph to have a different y-scale. This option is meaningless with -one!
Don't plot the connecting lines.

docs.title: No Connecting Lines
docs.description: Don't plot the connecting lines.

docs.title: No Connecting Lines with Axis Containment
docs.description: Same as -noline, but will not try to plot values outside the rectangular box that contains the graph axes.

docs.title: Plot Boxes
docs.description: Plot a small 'box' at each data point.

docs.title: Histogram Style
docs.description: Plot graphs in histogram style (i.e., vertical boxes).

docs.title: L2 Norm Scaling
docs.description: Independently scale each time series plotted to have L_2 norm = 1 (sum of squares).

docs.title: Linfinity Norm Scaling
docs.description: Independently scale each time series plotted to have max absolute value = 1 (L_infinity norm).

docs.title: L1 Norm Scaling
docs.description: Independently scale each time series plotted to have max sum of absolute values = 1 (L_1 norm).

docs.title: Demean Time Series
docs.description: Remove the mean from each time series before normalizing.

docs.title: X axis data
docs.description: Use for X axis the data in a specified .1D file.

docs.title: Log10 X axis data
docs.description: Use log10 of the specified .1D file as the X axis.

docs.title: X-axis spacing
docs.description: Spacing between points on the x-axis.

docs.title: Initial X coordinate
docs.description: Initial x coordinate.

docs.title: No Axis Pushing
docs.description: Don't 'push' axes ranges outwards.

docs.title: Ignore Initial Rows
docs.description: Skip first 'nn' rows in the input file.

docs.title: Use Specified Points
docs.description: Plot 'mm' points.

docs.title: X-axis Label
docs.description: Put string 'aa' below the x-axis.

docs.title: Y-axis Label
docs.description: Put string 'aa' to the left of the y-axis.

docs.title: Plot Label
docs.description: Put string 'pp' atop the plot.

docs.title: Plot Title
docs.description: Same as -plabel, but only works with -ps/-png/-jpg/-pnm options.

docs.title: Window Title
docs.description: Set string 'pp' as the title of the frame containing the plot.

docs.title: Naked Graph
docs.description: Do NOT plot axes or labels, just the graph(s).

docs.title: Aspect Ratio
docs.description: Set the width-to-height ratio of the plot region to 'A'.

docs.title: Read from Stdin
docs.description: Don't read from tsfile; instead, read from stdin and plot it.

docs.title: PostScript Output
docs.description: Don't draw plot in a window; instead, write it to stdout in PostScript format.

docs.title: JPEG Output
docs.description: Render plot to JPEG image and save to a file named 'fname'.

docs.title: JPEG Output
docs.description: Render plot to JPEG image and save to a file named 'fname'.

docs.title: PNG Output
docs.description: Render plot to PNG image and save to a file named 'fname'.

docs.title: PNM Output
docs.description: Render plot to PNM image and save to a file named 'fname'.

docs.title: PNG Output with Size
docs.description: Render plot to PNG image of specified size and save to a file named 'fname'.

docs.title: JPEG Output with Size
docs.description: Render plot to JPEG image of specified size and save to a file named 'fname'.

docs.title: JPEG Output with Size
docs.description: Render plot to JPEG image of specified size and save to a file named 'fname'.

docs.title: PNM Output with Size
docs.description: Render plot to PNM image of specified size and save to a file named 'fname'.

docs.title: Y-axis Transformation
docs.description: Transform the data along the y-axis by applying the expression to each input value.

docs.title: X-axis Transformation
docs.description: Transform the data along the x-axis by applying the expression to each input value.

docs.title: X-axis Settings
docs.description: Set the x-axis to run from value 'b' to value 't', with 'n' major divisions and 'm' minor tic marks per major division.

docs.title: Y-axis Settings
docs.description: Set the y-axis to run from value 'b' to value 't', with 'n' major divisions and 'm' minor tic marks per major division.

docs.title: Y-axis Names
docs.description: Use the strings as labels to the right of the graphs, corresponding to each input column.

docs.title: Volume Registration Names
docs.description: Makes the 'ynames' be the same as the 6 labels used in plug_volreg for Roll, Pitch, Yaw, I-S, R-L, and A-P movements.
Increase the line thickness used for plotting.

docs.title: Increase Line Thickness
docs.description: Increase the line thickness used for plotting.

docs.title: Double Line Thickness
docs.description: Twice the power of '-thick' at no extra cost!

docs.title: Dashed Lines
docs.description: Plot dashed lines between data points using specified colon-separated list of dash values (1: solid, 2: longer dashes, 3: shorter dashes).

docs.title: Set Environment Variable
docs.description: Set environment variable 'name' to 'val' for this run of the program only.

docs.title: Censor Marking Color
docs.description: Set the color used for marking to a specified color.

docs.title: Censor Time Series
docs.description: Specify the filename of the censor .1D time series.

docs.title: Censor Time Indexes
docs.description: Specify time indexes to be marked in the graph(s).

docs.title: Concatenated Runs
docs.description: Specify the filename for the list of concatenated runs.
Draw a rectangular box.

docs.title: Draw Rectangular Box
docs.description: Draw a rectangular box with specified corners and colors.

docs.title: Draw Rectangular Box with Line
docs.description: Draw a rectangular box with one extra horizontal line.

docs.title: Draw Line Segment
docs.description: Draw one line segment.

docs.title: 1dplot
docs.description: Graphs the columns of a *.1D time series file to the X11 screen, or to an image file (.jpg or .png).
